    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-27T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-27T08:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/1076: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-27T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 27, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 27—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>368. Reference Department’s telegram No. 154, April 26, 6 p.m. Foreign Office
                    this morning read to Embassy representative pertinent portion of instructions
                    sent Embassy at Washington concerning commercial treaty negotiations which
                    corresponds verbatim with statement delivered by Garreau-Dombasle. Am informed
                    that Minister of Commerce gave his prior approval to instructions and is
                    inclined to cooperate with Foreign Office in meeting so far as possible American
                    desiderata.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office optimistic and feels that if a substantial reduction in tariff on
                    champagne is granted it will greatly assist in securing advantages from French
                    Ministry of Agriculture. French Government very anxious that public notice of
                    intention to negotiate be made prior to coming into force of United
                    States-Belgian treaty.</p>
                <p>Laboulaye lunching alone with me and should further observations prove advisable
                    as a result of meeting will again cable the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
